Zeta Reticuli

There really is no place like Zeta Reticuli.

As home worlds go, the twin suns of Zeta Reticuli have a reputation amongst Galactic Merchants as being a quiet and
unassuming place; almost boring. As home worlds go, the twin suns of Zeta Reticuli have a reputation amongst Galactic
Merchants as being a quiet and unassuming place, almost boring.

It is very difficult to get to, as it is quite a long, long, long way from anywhere useful. It takes nearly a year travelling at Mega-
Warp speed to reach the vicinity, and even then you are likely to overshoot and find yourself heading straight into an astral
abyss, with no chance of setting a return course before your fuel runs out.

Zeta Reticuli does have many redeeming features, not the least of which is its unique flora and fauna. Zeta Reticuli does have
many redeeming features, not the least of which is its unique flora and fauna. The creatures that inhabit the main system are
mostly harmless, if a little noisy at night, most especially the small furry creatures that yelp all the time.

The climate, overall, is similar to that of Earth, with a few minor differences. The climate, overall, is similar to that of Earth,
with a few minor differences.

Zeta Reticuli receives a very large amount of radiation from its two suns. Zeta Reticuli receives a very large amount of
radiation from its two suns. This is mostly blocked by the strange makeup of the atmosphere, which contains a unique
element that reflects the harmful rays effectively.

A peculiar side effect of sitting between two suns, however, is that Zeta Reticuli has, quite literally, no darkness. A peculiar side
effect of sitting between two suns, however, is that Zeta Reticuli has, quite literally, no darkness. Instead, the inhabitants enjoy
a kind of twilight that, at its darkest, is not unlike a very overcast day on Earth.

There is only one main settlement on Zeta Reticuli, as the rest of the planet has been declared a wildlife preserve. There is
only one main settlement on Zeta Reticuli, as the rest of the planet has been declared a wildlife preserve. The settlement
itself, though, is something of a paradise. Free from the shackles of corporate and political meddling, the inhabitants enjoy
a completely free society, in which crime, poverty and suffering are virtually unheard of.

In short, Zeta Reticuli is the most wonderful place in the universe. In short, Zeta Reticuli is the most wonderful place in the
universe.
